<p><b>Incorporation</b> (abbreviated <b>Inc.</b> in <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">U.S.</a>, <a href="/wiki/Canadian" title="Canadian" class="mw-redirect">Canadian</a> and <a href="/wiki/Australian" title="Australian" class="mw-redirect">Australian</a> business names) is the forming of a new <a href="/wiki/Corporation" title="Corporation">corporation</a> (a corporation being a legal entity that is effectively <a href="/wiki/Legal_person" title="Legal person">recognised as a person under the law</a>). The corporation may be a business, a <a href="/wiki/Non-profit_organization" title="Non-profit organization">non-profit organization</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sports_club" title="Sports club">sports club</a> or a <a href="/wiki/Government" title="Government">government</a> of a new <a href="/wiki/City" title="City">city</a> or <a href="/wiki/Town" title="Town">town</a>. This article focuses on the process of incorporation; see also <a href="/wiki/Corporation" title="Corporation">corporation</a>.</p>
